Balance and Weights, Large Measures (to.Name: Balance and Weights, Large Measures (to 10 lb)

Tower Shield.Name: Tower Shield
Tower Shield.Description: A Tower Shield is a large, rectangular shield made of wood or metal, typically used in medieval warfare. It is designed to protect the user from incoming projectiles and melee attacks, and is held in front of the body with both hands. It is usually taller than the user, and can be used to protect multiple people at once.

Padded Suit.Name: Padded Suit
Padded Suit.Description: A Padded Suit is a type of armour made from quilted fabric, usually wool, cotton, or linen, which is filled with soft materials such as wool, cotton, or horsehair. It is designed to provide protection against slashing and piercing weapons, as well as providing some cushioning against blunt force trauma. It is often worn over a gambeson or other type of armour for additional protection.

Quilted Suit.Name: Quilted Suit
Quilted Suit.Description: A Quilted Suit is a type of armour made from multiple layers of fabric, usually cotton or linen, that are stitched together to form a protective layer. The quilted fabric is usually padded with a layer of wool or other material to provide additional protection. Quilted suits are often used in reenactment and historical combat, as well as in some modern martial arts.

Hide Suit.Name: Hide Suit
Hide Suit.Description: A Hide Suit is a type of armour made from animal hide, usually from cows, pigs, or horses. It is usually made up of several layers of hide sewn together and is designed to provide protection from physical attacks. It is often used in reenactment and LARPing, as well as in some martial arts.

Leather Suit.Name: Leather Suit
Leather Suit.Description: Leather suits are a type of armor made from leather, usually cowhide. They are lightweight and flexible, providing protection from cuts and scrapes while still allowing for a full range of motion. Leather suits are often used in reenactment and theatrical performances, as well as in some martial arts.

Studded Leather Suit.Name: Studded Leather Suit
Studded Leather Suit.Description: A Studded Leather Suit is a type of armour made from leather and reinforced with metal studs. It provides protection from physical attacks and is often used by warriors and adventurers. It is lightweight and flexible, allowing for greater mobility than heavier armours.

Ring Mail Suit.Name: Ring Mail Suit
Ring Mail Suit.Description: Ring mail is a type of armour made from interlocking metal rings, typically of iron or steel. It was used in the Middle Ages and was the predecessor to the more advanced plate armour. It provided good protection against slashing and piercing weapons, but was less effective against blunt force trauma.

Brigandine Suit.Name: Brigandine Suit
Brigandine Suit.Description: A Brigandine Suit is a type of armour consisting of a series of metal plates riveted to a fabric or leather backing. It was popular in the 15th and 16th centuries and was often used by soldiers and mercenaries. It provided good protection against slashing and piercing weapons, while still allowing for some flexibility and mobility.

Chain Mail Suit.Name: Chain Mail Suit
Chain Mail Suit.Description: A Chain Mail Suit is a type of armour made up of interlocking metal rings, typically made of iron or steel. It was used in medieval times to protect the wearer from swords, arrows, and other weapons. It is still used today in some forms of martial arts and reenactment.

Scale Mail Suit.Name: Scale Mail Suit
Scale Mail Suit.Description: Scale mail is a type of armour made up of small metal scales sewn onto a fabric backing. It is lightweight and flexible, providing protection from slashing and piercing weapons. It is often worn over a padded gambeson for additional protection.

Splint Mail Suit.Name: Splint Mail Suit
Splint Mail Suit.Description: Splint mail is a type of armour made from overlapping metal strips, or splints, that are riveted together to form a flexible, yet protective, garment. It was used in Europe from the 12th to the 16th centuries and was typically worn over a padded garment. Splint mail was lighter and more flexible than plate armour, making it easier to move in, but it was still strong enough to protect against swords and arrows.

Banded Mail Suit.Name: Banded Mail Suit
Banded Mail Suit.Description: A Banded Mail Suit is a type of armour consisting of small metal rings linked together to form a protective layer. It is typically worn over a padded garment and is designed to protect the wearer from slashing and piercing attacks. It is a popular choice for medieval re-enactors and is often seen in fantasy films and games.

Plate Mail Suit.Name: Plate Mail Suit
Plate Mail Suit.Description: Plate Mail is a type of armour made from metal plates that are riveted together. It is typically worn over a padded or quilted garment, and is designed to protect the wearer from physical attacks. Plate Mail is usually made from steel, but can also be made from other metals such as bronze or iron. It is one of the most protective types of armour, and was commonly used by knights and other warriors during the Middle Ages.

Field Plate Mail Suit.Name: Field Plate Mail Suit
Field Plate Mail Suit.Description: Field Plate Mail Suit is a type of armour that was used in the Middle Ages. It consists of a full body suit of metal plates, usually made of iron or steel, that are connected together with leather straps or rivets. The plates are designed to protect the wearer from swords, arrows, and other weapons. It is usually worn over a padded gambeson or aketon for additional protection.

Full Plate Mail Suit.Name: Full Plate Mail Suit
Full Plate Mail Suit.Description: Full Plate Mail is a type of armour consisting of a full body suit of metal plates, typically made of steel, covering the torso, arms, and legs. It is designed to provide maximum protection against physical attacks, and is often used by knights and other warriors in battle.

Medium Shield.Name: Medium Shield
Medium Shield.Description: A Medium Shield is a type of Armour that is typically made of metal or wood and is used to protect the body from physical attacks. It is usually held in the hand or strapped to the arm and is designed to absorb or deflect blows from weapons such as swords, spears, and arrows.

Buckler.Name: Buckler
Buckler.Description: A buckler is a small, round shield typically made of metal or wood and used to protect the body from attack. It is usually held in the left hand and used to deflect blows from swords, spears, and other weapons. Bucklers are often used in conjunction with a sword or other weapon in one-on-one combat.

1 Week Medieval Cooking Supplies.Name: 1 Week Medieval Cooking Supplies
1 Week Medieval Cooking Supplies.Description: A 1 Week Medieval Cooking Supplies set is a collection of essential cooking tools for preparing meals in a medieval kitchen. It typically includes a large cauldron, a variety of spoons, ladles, and other utensils, a mortar and pestle, a grater, a sieve, a cheesecloth, and a variety of other items. This set of tools is essential for preparing traditional medieval dishes such as stews, soups, and sauces.

Fire grate.Name: Fire grate
Fire grate.Description: A fire grate is a type of cooking tool used to hold burning fuel such as wood, charcoal, or coal. It is typically made of metal and has a grate-like surface that allows air to circulate around the fuel, allowing it to burn more efficiently. Fire grates are commonly used in outdoor cooking, such as barbecuing, and can also be used indoors in fireplaces.

Fishhook.Name: Fishhook
Fishhook.Description: A fishhook is a type of cooking tool used to hold food items such as fish, vegetables, and other items while they are being cooked. It is typically made of metal and has a curved hook at one end that is used to secure the food item. Fishhooks are often used in grilling, frying, and other cooking methods.

Iron Pan (Frying).Name: Iron Pan (Frying)
Iron Pan (Frying).Description: An iron pan (frying pan) is a type of cooking tool used for frying, sautéing, and other cooking techniques. It is typically made of cast iron and has a flat bottom and sloped sides, allowing for even heat distribution. It is a versatile tool that can be used on a variety of heat sources, including stovetops, grills, and campfires.

Iron Pot.Name: Iron Pot
Iron Pot.Description: An iron pot is a type of cooking tool that is made of cast iron and is used for a variety of cooking tasks. It is a heavy-duty pot that is great for slow-cooking stews, soups, and other dishes that require long cooking times. Iron pots are also great for braising, frying, and boiling. They are durable and can last for many years with proper care.

1 Week's Dry Rations.Name: 1 Week's Dry Rations
1 Week's Dry Rations.Description: A 1 Week's Dry Rations is a type of cooking tool that provides a convenient and easy way to store and prepare meals for up to one week. It typically includes a variety of non-perishable food items such as canned goods, dried fruits, nuts, grains, and other items that can be stored for long periods of time without spoiling. The rations are designed to provide a balanced diet and can be used in a variety of situations, such as camping, hiking, and emergency preparedness.

1 Week's Elven Waybread.Name: 1 Week's Elven Waybread
1 Week's Elven Waybread.Description: Elven Waybread is a type of cooking tool used to make a traditional elven bread. It is a round, flat, and thin disc made of clay or stone, with a hole in the center. It is used to bake a type of unleavened bread that is traditionally eaten during festivals and celebrations. The bread is made with flour, water, and salt, and is cooked over an open fire. The bread is usually served with honey or jam, and is a popular snack among elves.

Standard (perishable), 1 Day.Name: Standard (perishable), 1 Day
Standard (perishable), 1 Day.Description: A Standard (perishable) 1 Day Cooking Tool is a tool designed to be used for a single day of cooking. It is typically made of a material that is not designed to last for long periods of time, such as plastic or wood. These tools are often used for quick and easy cooking tasks, such as chopping vegetables, stirring sauces, and forming dough. They are also often used for more complex tasks, such as baking and roasting.

Tea pot.Name: Tea pot
Tea pot.Description: A teapot is a type of cooking tool used for brewing and serving tea. It typically consists of a handle, spout, lid, and body, and is made from a variety of materials such as ceramic, glass, metal, or plastic. Teapots are often decorated with intricate designs and come in a variety of sizes and shapes.

Tripod.Name: Tripod
Tripod.Description: A tripod is a type of cooking tool that consists of three legs that are connected at the top. It is used to suspend a pot or pan over a fire or other heat source. It is often used for outdoor cooking, such as camping or barbecuing.

Small bag of coloured chalk pieces.Name: Small bag of coloured chalk pieces

Small bag of white chalk pieces.Name: Small bag of white chalk pieces

Hood or Cowl, Wool or Linen.Name: Hood or Cowl, Wool or Linen

Punch.Name: Punch
Punch.Description: A punch is a type of weapon consisting of a short, rigid object, usually with a handle, used to strike an opponent. It is typically used in martial arts and boxing, but can also be used in self-defense.

Gauntlet.Name: Gauntlet
Gauntlet.Description: A Gauntlet is a type of weapon consisting of a metal glove that covers the hand and forearm. It is typically used in close-quarters combat and is designed to protect the wearer's hand and arm from slashing and piercing attacks.

Pommel.Name: Pommel
Pommel.Description: A pommel is a type of weapon consisting of a handle or hilt with a rounded or pointed end. It is typically used in swords, daggers, and other bladed weapons to provide balance and leverage when thrusting or slashing.

Kick.Name: Kick
Kick.Description: A kick is a type of weapon used in martial arts and self-defense. It is a powerful strike with the foot or leg, usually aimed at an opponent's body or head. Kicks can be used to knock an opponent off balance, to create distance, or to inflict damage.

Great Axe.Name: Great Axe
Great Axe.Description: A Great Axe is a large two-handed axe with a long handle and a wide, curved blade. It is a powerful weapon capable of delivering devastating blows, and is often used by warriors and adventurers alike.

Two-Handed Sword.Name: Two-Handed Sword
Two-Handed Sword.Description: A two-handed sword is a large, heavy sword that requires two hands to wield. It is typically used for slashing and thrusting attacks, and is often used in medieval combat. It is usually longer than a one-handed sword, and its weight and size make it more difficult to wield.

Maul.Name: Maul
Maul.Description: A maul is a type of weapon consisting of a heavy, long-handled hammer with a metal head. It is used for smashing, crushing, and pounding objects, and is often used in woodworking and construction.

Great Mace.Name: Great Mace
Great Mace.Description: A Great Mace is a type of weapon consisting of a long wooden or metal shaft with a heavy, spiked metal head. It is used to deliver powerful blows to an opponent, and is often used in close-quarters combat.

Great Flail.Name: Great Flail
Great Flail.Description: A Great Flail is a type of weapon consisting of a long wooden handle with a metal head attached to it by a chain or rope. The head is usually spiked or studded with metal, and the weapon is swung in a circular motion to inflict damage on an opponent.

Polearm.Name: Polearm
Polearm.Description: A polearm is a type of weapon consisting of a long shaft with a sharpened blade or point at one end. It is usually used in close combat, and is often used to thrust, hook, or sweep an opponent. Polearms are usually used in pairs, and can be used to great effect against cavalry and infantry.

Quarterstaff.Name: Quarterstaff
Quarterstaff.Description: A Quarterstaff is a type of weapon consisting of a long wooden staff, typically between 5 and 8 feet in length. It is a versatile weapon, capable of being used for thrusting, striking, and blocking. It is a popular weapon in martial arts, and is often used in historical reenactments.

Lance.Name: Lance
Lance.Description: A lance is a type of polearm weapon consisting of a long wooden shaft with a pointed metal head. It was used by cavalry during the Middle Ages and Renaissance, and is still used in some modern sports such as jousting.

Greatclub.Name: Greatclub
Greatclub.Description: A Greatclub is a two-handed bludgeoning weapon made of a large, heavy wooden club. It is typically used to deliver powerful blows in close combat, and is often used by warriors and barbarians.

Scythe.Name: Scythe
Scythe.Description: A scythe is a long-handled agricultural tool used for cutting grass, grain, or other crops. As a weapon, it is a polearm with a curved blade at the end, used for slashing and hacking. It is typically wielded with two hands and is associated with death and the Grim Reaper.

One-Handed Spear.Name: One-Handed Spear
One-Handed Spear.Description: A one-handed spear is a type of weapon that consists of a long shaft with a pointed tip at one end and a handle at the other. It is typically used for thrusting and stabbing, and can be used in both one-handed and two-handed combat. It is a versatile weapon that can be used in a variety of situations, from hunting to self-defense.

One-Handed Fork.Name: One-Handed Fork
One-Handed Fork.Description: A one-handed fork is a type of weapon that consists of a long handle with a short, curved prong at the end. It is typically used in close-quarters combat, and can be used to stab, slash, and hook an opponent. It is also sometimes used as a tool for grappling and disarming an opponent.

One-Handed Trident.Name: One-Handed Trident
One-Handed Trident.Description: A One-Handed Trident is a type of weapon consisting of a three-pronged spear with a long shaft. It is designed to be wielded with one hand, allowing the wielder to use their other hand for a shield or other weapon. It is a versatile weapon, capable of thrusting, slashing, and hooking attacks.

One-Handed Boar Spear.Name: One-Handed Boar Spear
One-Handed Boar Spear.Description: A One-Handed Boar Spear is a type of weapon designed for hunting wild boar. It is a long, slender spear with a single-edged blade at the end, designed to penetrate the thick hide of a boar. The shaft is usually made of wood or metal, and the blade is usually made of steel. The spear is typically used in a thrusting motion, and is often used in combination with a shield or other defensive weapon.

Two-Handed Spear.Name: Two-Handed Spear
Two-Handed Spear.Description: A Two-Handed Spear is a type of weapon that is typically used in close-quarters combat. It consists of a long shaft with a sharpened point at one end and a crossguard at the other. The crossguard is used to protect the wielder's hands from an opponent's weapon. The long shaft allows the wielder to keep their opponent at a distance and to thrust and stab with the spear.

Two-Handed Fork.Name: Two-Handed Fork
Two-Handed Fork.Description: A Two-Handed Fork is a type of weapon that consists of two long metal prongs attached to a handle. It is typically used in martial arts and fencing, and is designed to be held in both hands for increased reach and power. It can be used to thrust, parry, and block attacks, and can also be used to disarm an opponent.

Two-Handed Trident.Name: Two-Handed Trident
Two-Handed Trident.Description: A Two-Handed Trident is a type of weapon consisting of a long shaft with three sharp prongs at the end. It is typically used in close-quarters combat, and is capable of piercing armor and inflicting serious damage. It is also a popular weapon in many fantasy settings.

Two-Handed Boar Spear.Name: Two-Handed Boar Spear
Two-Handed Boar Spear.Description: A Two-Handed Boar Spear is a type of weapon designed for hunting wild boar. It is a long spear with a wide, double-edged blade at the end, and a long handle with two grips. The blade is designed to penetrate the thick hide of a boar, while the long handle allows for greater reach and power when thrusting.

Whip.Name: Whip
Whip.Description: A whip is a type of weapon consisting of a long, flexible strip of leather or other material, usually with a handle at one end, used to inflict pain or punishment on a person or animal. It is often used as a tool of discipline or punishment, and can be used to inflict physical or psychological pain.

Club.Name: Club
Club.Description: A club is a blunt weapon consisting of a short, heavy piece of wood or metal, typically with one end thicker or heavier than the other. It is used for striking an opponent in hand-to-hand combat, or as a means of self-defense.

Cudgel.Name: Cudgel
Cudgel.Description: A cudgel is a short, blunt club-like weapon typically made of wood or metal. It is used for self-defense or as a tool for striking an opponent. It is usually wielded with one hand and can be used to deliver powerful blows to an opponent.

Walking Staff.Name: Walking Staff
Walking Staff.Description: A Walking Staff is a type of weapon that consists of a long, wooden pole with a pointed end. It is typically used for self-defense and can be used to strike, jab, or block an opponent. It is also commonly used as a walking aid.

Silver Walking Stick†.Name: Silver Walking Stick†
Silver Walking Stick†.Description: A Silver Walking Stick is a type of weapon that is typically made of a metal such as silver and is used as a defensive tool. It is usually a long, straight stick with a handle at one end and a pointed tip at the other. It can be used to block or parry an attack, or to strike an opponent.

Silver Walking Staff†.Name: Silver Walking Staff†
Silver Walking Staff†.Description: A Silver Walking Staff is a type of weapon that is typically made of silver and is used as a walking aid. It is usually a long, straight staff with a curved handle at one end and a pointed tip at the other. It can be used as a defensive weapon, as it can be used to block and parry attacks, as well as to strike an opponent.

Spade.Name: Spade
Spade.Description: A spade is a type of weapon that consists of a long, sharp blade with a handle attached to it. It is typically used for digging, but can also be used as a slashing or stabbing weapon.

Crowbar.Name: Crowbar
Crowbar.Description: A crowbar is a type of weapon consisting of a metal bar with a single curved end and flattened points, often with a small fissure on one or both ends for removing nails. It is used as a lever to pry objects apart or to force them open.

Pitchfork.Name: Pitchfork
Pitchfork.Description: A Pitchfork is a type of weapon consisting of a long handle with two or more metal tines at the end. It is typically used as a farming tool, but can also be used as a weapon in close combat. It is a versatile weapon, capable of thrusting, slashing, and parrying attacks.

Battle Axe.Name: Battle Axe
Battle Axe.Description: A Battle Axe is a type of weapon consisting of a heavy, usually double-headed axe blade mounted on a long handle. It was used in close combat and was a common weapon of choice in the Middle Ages. Battle axes were used to deliver powerful blows and could be used to cut through armor and shields.

Mattock.Name: Mattock
Mattock.Description: A mattock is a type of weapon consisting of a long handle with a heavy, pointed head at one end. It is used for digging, chopping, and breaking up hard surfaces such as soil, rocks, and roots. It is also used as a weapon in some martial arts.

Longsword.Name: Longsword
Longsword.Description: A longsword is a type of weapon that is characterized by a long, double-edged blade with a hilt that is usually designed to be gripped with two hands. It is a versatile weapon that can be used for slashing, thrusting, and parrying. It is a popular weapon in many forms of martial arts and historical European martial arts.

Scimitar.Name: Scimitar
Scimitar.Description: A scimitar is a type of curved sword with a single-edged blade that is usually used for slashing and cutting. It is characterized by its curved blade and sharp point, and is often associated with Middle Eastern and North African cultures.

Mace.Name: Mace
Mace.Description: A mace is a type of weapon consisting of a heavy head on a handle or shaft, used for striking or bludgeoning. It is typically made of metal, wood, or stone, and can be used for both offensive and defensive purposes.

Morningstar.Name: Morningstar
Morningstar.Description: A Morningstar is a type of medieval weapon consisting of a spiked metal ball attached to a wooden or metal handle. It was used to bludgeon and crush opponents in close combat, and was often used to break through armor.

Flail.Name: Flail
Flail.Description: A flail is a type of weapon consisting of a handle attached to a spiked head by a chain or rope. It is used to strike opponents with the spiked head, and can be used to entangle or disarm them.

Chain.Name: Chain
Chain.Description: A chain is a type of weapon consisting of a length of metal links or rings connected together. It is usually used as a flail, whip, or garrote, and can be used to entangle an opponent or to deliver a powerful blow. Chains can also be used to bind an opponent, or to create a makeshift weapon such as a flail or whip.

Torch (fire damage).Name: Torch (fire damage)
Torch (fire damage).Description: A Torch is a type of weapon that deals fire damage. It is a handheld device that is lit and used to set enemies ablaze. It is a common weapon used by adventurers and warriors alike, and is often used to light dark areas or to set objects on fire.

Cestus.Name: Cestus
Cestus.Description: A Cestus is a type of weapon used in Ancient Greece and Rome. It is a type of glove with metal plates or spikes attached to the knuckles, designed to increase the power of punches and cause more damage to an opponent.

Spiked Gauntlet.Name: Spiked Gauntlet
Spiked Gauntlet.Description: A Spiked Gauntlet is a type of weapon consisting of a metal glove with spikes protruding from the knuckles. It is designed to increase the damage inflicted by punches and can be used in close-quarters combat.

Dagger.Name: Dagger
Dagger.Description: A dagger is a short-bladed weapon with a sharp point, typically designed for thrusting or stabbing. It is usually double-edged and has a hilt or handle for gripping. Daggers have been used throughout history for close combat and self-defense.

Defending Dagger.Name: Defending Dagger
Defending Dagger.Description: A Defending Dagger is a type of weapon designed for close-quarters combat. It is a short, double-edged blade with a guard to protect the user's hand from an opponent's weapon. It is typically used for thrusting and slashing attacks, and is often used in conjunction with a shield or buckler.

Silver Dagger†.Name: Silver Dagger†
Silver Dagger†.Description: A Silver Dagger is a type of weapon that consists of a short blade with a hilt made of silver. It is typically used as a thrusting weapon, and is often used in close-quarters combat. Silver Daggers are often decorated with intricate designs and are considered to be a symbol of power and prestige.

Sap.Name: Sap
Sap.Description: A sap is a type of weapon consisting of a heavy leather or rubber tube filled with lead shot or other heavy material. It is used to deliver a powerful, non-lethal blow to an opponent, usually to the head or upper body. It is often used by law enforcement officers as a less-than-lethal alternative to firearms.

Frying Pan.Name: Frying Pan
Frying Pan.Description: A Frying Pan is a type of weapon that is typically used as a blunt force instrument. It is usually made of metal and has a flat, round surface. It is often used to strike an opponent, and can be used to block or deflect attacks.

Blackjack.Name: Blackjack
Blackjack.Description: Blackjack is a type of weapon consisting of a short, leather-wrapped club with a heavy, weighted end. It is typically used to deliver a quick, non-lethal blow to an attacker, and is often used by law enforcement officers and security personnel.

Hand Axe.Name: Hand Axe
Hand Axe.Description: A hand axe is a type of weapon that consists of a sharpened stone or metal blade attached to a handle. It is a versatile tool that can be used for cutting, chopping, and scraping. It is an ancient tool that has been used for thousands of years and is still used today in some parts of the world.

Pickaxe.Name: Pickaxe
Pickaxe.Description: A pickaxe is a type of weapon consisting of a long handle with a metal head at one end, typically with a pointed end and a flat end. It is used for breaking up rocks and other hard materials, such as ice or soil. It can also be used as a weapon in close combat, as it can be used to strike an opponent.

Shortsword.Name: Shortsword
Shortsword.Description: A shortsword is a type of weapon that is typically shorter than a longsword, with a blade length of around 30 inches. It is a versatile weapon, capable of both slashing and thrusting attacks, and is often used in close-quarters combat. It is also light and easy to wield, making it a popular choice for adventurers and warriors alike.

Cutlass.Name: Cutlass
Cutlass.Description: A cutlass is a short, curved sword with a single-edged blade. It was commonly used by sailors and pirates in the 16th to 19th centuries. It is characterized by its heavy, curved blade and basket-shaped hilt, which provided protection for the hand.

Warhammer.Name: Warhammer
Warhammer.Description: A Warhammer is a type of weapon consisting of a heavy metal head attached to a wooden or metal handle. It is typically used as a two-handed weapon, and is designed to deliver powerful blows to an enemy. It is commonly used in fantasy settings, such as in the popular tabletop game Warhammer.

Light Mace.Name: Light Mace
Light Mace.Description: A light mace is a type of weapon consisting of a short wooden or metal shaft with a heavy head, usually made of metal, at one end. It is used for bludgeoning and is typically wielded with one hand.

Hook.Name: Hook
Hook.Description: A hook is a type of weapon that consists of a curved metal blade with a sharp point at the end. It is typically used to catch and hold an opponent, allowing the wielder to control the fight. Hooks can also be used to disarm an opponent, as well as to inflict serious wounds.

Sickle.Name: Sickle
Sickle.Description: A Sickle is a curved blade weapon with a short handle, traditionally used for harvesting crops but also used as a weapon in some cultures. It is characterized by its curved blade, which is sharp on the inside edge and can be used to slash or hook an opponent.

Random Object.Name: Random Object
Random Object.Description: A Random Object Weapon is a type of weapon that is made from everyday objects that can be found around the home or in the environment. These weapons can range from a heavy book to a sharpened stick, and can be used to defend oneself in a dangerous situation.

Light Barding.Name: Light Barding
Light Barding.Description: Light barding is a type of mount armor designed to protect horses and other mounts from light attacks. It is typically made of leather or metal plates and covers the horse's head, neck, chest, and flanks. It is lighter than traditional barding and is often used for riding in tournaments or jousts.

Mail Barding.Name: Mail Barding
Mail Barding.Description: Mail Barding is a type of Mount Armour that is designed to protect a horse from attack. It is made of interlocking metal rings, usually of iron or steel, that are linked together to form a protective covering. It is typically worn over a horse's head, neck, chest, and flanks, and can also be used to protect the horse's legs.

Plate Barding.Name: Plate Barding
Plate Barding.Description: Plate barding is a type of mount armor that is designed to protect horses from injury in battle. It consists of metal plates that are attached to the horse's body, usually covering the head, neck, chest, and flanks. The plates are usually made of steel or iron and are often decorated with intricate designs. Plate barding was used by knights and other mounted warriors during the Middle Ages and Renaissance periods.

Simple Scribe kit (quill & tools, writin.Name: Simple Scribe kit (quill & tools, writing board)

Dart.Name: Dart
Dart.Description: A dart is a small, lightweight projectile weapon that is thrown by hand. It typically consists of a pointed tip made of metal, wood, or plastic, and a shaft made of wood, plastic, or fiberglass. Darts are used in a variety of sports, such as darts, target shooting, and hunting.

Hand Quarrel.Name: Hand Quarrel
Hand Quarrel.Description: A hand quarrel is a type of weapon consisting of a short, metal-tipped shaft with a small, round head. It is typically used in close-quarters combat and is designed to be thrown at an opponent. The head of the quarrel is designed to penetrate armor and cause serious injury.

Silver Hand Quarrel†.Name: Silver Hand Quarrel†
Silver Hand Quarrel†.Description: A Silver Hand Quarrel is a type of weapon used in the Middle Ages. It is a type of crossbow bolt, usually made of steel, with a silver hand-shaped head. It was designed to penetrate armor and cause maximum damage. The Silver Hand Quarrel was a popular weapon among knights and other warriors during the Middle Ages.

Stone.Name: Stone
Stone.Description: A stone is a primitive weapon that has been used since ancient times. It is a simple, yet effective tool for hunting and self-defense. Stones can be thrown, used as a club, or even sharpened to create a cutting edge. They are still used in some parts of the world today.

Bullet.Name: Bullet
Bullet.Description: A bullet is a type of weapon that is typically a small, metal projectile fired from a gun. Bullets are typically made of lead, copper, or steel and are designed to cause damage to a target upon impact.

Silver Bullet†.Name: Silver Bullet†
Silver Bullet†.Description: A Silver Bullet is a type of weapon that is believed to be able to kill supernatural creatures such as werewolves, vampires, and other monsters. It is usually made of silver and is often used in folklore and mythology. It is believed that the silver bullet is the only weapon that can kill these creatures, and it is often seen as a symbol of courage and strength.

Shortbow Arrow.Name: Shortbow Arrow
Shortbow Arrow.Description: A Shortbow Arrow is a type of weapon used in archery. It is a short, lightweight arrow with a small head, designed to be fired from a shortbow. It is typically used for hunting and target practice.

Silver Shortbow Arrow†.Name: Silver Shortbow Arrow†
Silver Shortbow Arrow†.Description: The Silver Shortbow Arrow is a type of weapon used in archery. It is a lightweight arrow made of silver-plated steel, with a short, curved bow and a sharp, pointed tip. It is designed for accuracy and speed, and is often used in hunting and target shooting.

Light Quarrel.Name: Light Quarrel
Light Quarrel.Description: A light quarrel is a type of weapon that is similar to a crossbow, but with a shorter range and lighter construction. It is typically made of wood and metal, and is used to fire small projectiles such as arrows or bolts. It is often used in hunting and warfare, and is a popular choice for those looking for a lightweight and easy to use weapon.

Silver Light Quarrel †.Name: Silver Light Quarrel †
Silver Light Quarrel †.Description: A Silver Light Quarrel is a type of weapon used in archery. It is a type of arrow with a silver-tipped head, designed to be used with a crossbow. The silver tip is designed to cause more damage to the target than a regular arrowhead. Silver Light Quarrels are often used in hunting and warfare, and are favored by many archers for their accuracy and power.

Longbow Arrow.Name: Longbow Arrow
Longbow Arrow.Description: A Longbow Arrow is a type of weapon used in archery. It is typically made of wood and is longer than a regular arrow, measuring up to five feet in length. The arrowhead is usually made of metal and is designed to penetrate armor. Longbow arrows are used for hunting and warfare, and are known for their accuracy and power.

Silver Longbow Arrow†.Name: Silver Longbow Arrow†
Silver Longbow Arrow†.Description: A Silver Longbow Arrow is a type of weapon used in archery. It is a longbow arrow made of silver, which is a metal known for its strength and durability. The arrowhead is usually made of steel and is designed to penetrate armor and other tough materials. Silver Longbow Arrows are often used in hunting and target shooting, and are known for their accuracy and power.

Heavy Quarrel.Name: Heavy Quarrel
Heavy Quarrel.Description: A Heavy Quarrel is a type of weapon that consists of a large, heavy arrow with a thick metal head. It is designed to penetrate armor and cause significant damage to its target. It is usually fired from a crossbow or a ballista.

Silver Heavy Quarrel†.Name: Silver Heavy Quarrel†
Silver Heavy Quarrel†.Description: A Silver Heavy Quarrel is a type of weapon used in the Middle Ages. It is a large, heavy crossbow bolt, usually made of iron or steel and tipped with a silver head. It was designed to penetrate armor and cause maximum damage to the target. It was often used in siege warfare and was a powerful and deadly weapon.

Longbow.Name: Longbow
Longbow.Description: A longbow is a type of weapon that is made from a single piece of wood, usually yew, and is used to shoot arrows. It is typically taller than a person and requires strength and skill to use effectively. Longbows were used in warfare and hunting in Europe and Asia from the Middle Ages to the early modern period.

Heavy Crossbow.Name: Heavy Crossbow
Heavy Crossbow.Description: A Heavy Crossbow is a type of weapon that is a large, powerful crossbow designed to fire heavy bolts with great force. It is usually made of metal and is often used for hunting or warfare. It is capable of firing bolts at a much greater distance than a regular crossbow and can penetrate armor.

Blowgun.Name: Blowgun
Blowgun.Description: A blowgun is a type of weapon consisting of a long, narrow tube through which a projectile, such as a dart or a pellet, is propelled by the force of the user's breath. It is used for hunting small game and as a recreational activity.

Net.Name: Net
Net.Description: Net as a weapon is a type of weapon used to entangle and immobilize an opponent. It is usually made of rope, chain, or metal links and is thrown at an opponent to ensnare them. Nets can be used in hand-to-hand combat, or as a ranged weapon. Nets are often used in martial arts and historical reenactments.

Javelin.Name: Javelin
Javelin.Description: A javelin is a type of spear-like throwing weapon used in ancient times. It consists of a long wooden shaft with a sharp metal tip, and is designed to be thrown at a target. Javelins were used in warfare and hunting, and were often used as a ranged weapon in hand-to-hand combat.

Bullet Crossbow.Name: Bullet Crossbow
Bullet Crossbow.Description: A Bullet Crossbow is a type of weapon that combines the power of a crossbow with the accuracy of a firearm. It uses a magazine-fed system to fire bullets instead of arrows, and is capable of firing multiple shots in quick succession. It is a powerful and accurate weapon, and is often used for hunting and target shooting.

Shortbow.Name: Shortbow
Shortbow.Description: A shortbow is a type of bow that is shorter than a traditional longbow. It is usually made of wood, and is used to shoot arrows at a target. It is a popular weapon for hunting and archery competitions.

Light Crossbow.Name: Light Crossbow
Light Crossbow.Description: A Light Crossbow is a type of weapon that is smaller and lighter than a standard crossbow. It is easy to use and reload, making it a popular choice for hunters and adventurers. It is capable of firing bolts at a range of up to 80 yards, and can be used to hunt small game or for self-defense.

Throwing Blade.Name: Throwing Blade
Throwing Blade.Description: A Throwing Blade is a type of weapon designed for throwing at a target. It is typically a flat, metal blade with a sharpened edge and a handle for gripping. Throwing blades can be used for hunting, self-defense, or as a sport. They are often used in martial arts and can be thrown with great accuracy and speed.

Sling.Name: Sling
Sling.Description: A sling is a type of weapon consisting of a Y-shaped frame with a pocket in the middle, used to hurl stones or other projectiles. It is believed to have been used since prehistoric times and is still used in some parts of the world today.

Bola.Name: Bola
Bola.Description: A Bola is a type of weapon consisting of two or more weights connected by a rope or cord. It is used to entangle an opponent's legs or arms, making them unable to move. Bolas are traditionally used by hunters and herders to capture animals, but have also been used as a weapon in combat.

Hand Crossbow.Name: Hand Crossbow
Hand Crossbow.Description: A Hand Crossbow is a small, handheld weapon that fires bolts or quarrels. It is a type of crossbow that is held in one hand and operated by a trigger mechanism. It is a popular weapon for hunters and adventurers due to its compact size and ease of use.

Random Object (thrown).Name: Random Object (thrown)
Random Object (thrown).Description: A random object thrown as a weapon could be a heavy book, a rock, or a bottle. These objects can be used to surprise an attacker and can cause serious injury if thrown with enough force.
